    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-12-08T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-12-08T05:00:00-05:00" n="598"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d598">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12209: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"
                            type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-12-08T18:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 8, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 8—3:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1307. Following from American Consul at Chefoo: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“December 8, 3 p.m. General <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_LC9">Liu
                                Chen-nien</persName> left here secretly early <pb facs="0654"
                                n="556" xml:id="pg_556"/> yesterday morning on the Chinese transport
                                <hi rend="italic">Tai Shun</hi> for Wenchow. He was accompanied by
                            General <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_TC3">Chao</persName>, staff and
                            bodyguard.</p>
                        <p>General <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_HI1">Ho I-san</persName> now in
                            charge of remainder of <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_LC9"
                                >Liu</persName>’s forces in this district numbering 8,000.
                            Transportation officer in charge of evacuation stated today all would be
                            out by end of December.</p>
                        <p>Chefoo quiet. <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_LC9">Liu</persName>’s
                            remaining forces maintaining excellent discipline and being gradually
                            moved towards Chefoo for embarkation.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_ECVH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
